# How does cuDNN version checking work in PyTorch? I need to understand how compile-time vs runtime cuDNN version is used for dispatching heuristics in SDPA (scaled dot product attention) and convolution operations. Specifically, I'm looking at exposing cuDNN runtime version in CUDA hooks.

Now I have a comprehensive understanding! Let me create a detailed response with all the key information.

## How cuDNN Version Checking Works in PyTorch

PyTorch uses a **dual-version system** for cuDNN: **compile-time** and **runtime** versions. Here's how it works:

### Core Version Retrieval Mechanisms

#### 1. **Compile-Time Version** ([`versionCuDNN()`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp?L347-L353))
Returns the `CUDNN_VERSION` macro that was available when PyTorch was compiled:

```cpp
long CUDAHooks::versionCuDNN() const {
#if AT_CUDNN_ENABLED()
  return CUDNN_VERSION;  // Compile-time constant
#else
  TORCH_CHECK(false, "Cannot query CuDNN version if ATen_cuda is not built with CuDNN");
#endif
}
```

#### 2. **Runtime Version** ([`versionRuntimeCuDNN()`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp?L355-L365))
Queries the actual cuDNN library loaded at runtime via `cudnnGetVersion()`:

```cpp
long CUDAHooks::versionRuntimeCuDNN() const {
#if AT_CUDNN_ENABLED()
#ifndef USE_STATIC_CUDNN
  return cudnnGetVersion();  // Runtime query
#else
  return CUDNN_VERSION;  // Static linking = compile version
#endif
#else
  TORCH_CHECK(false, "Cannot query CuDNN version if ATen_cuda is not built with CuDNN");
#endif
}
```

Both are exposed via the CUDA hooks interface in [`CUDAHooksInterface.h`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/aten/src/ATen/detail/CUDAHooksInterface.h?L173-L179).

### Python Bindings

The cuDNN version information is exposed to Python through [`torch/csrc/cuda/shared/cudnn.cpp`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/torch/csrc/cuda/shared/cudnn.cpp):

```cpp
version_tuple getCompileVersion() {
  return version_tuple(CUDNN_MAJOR, CUDNN_MINOR, CUDNN_PATCHLEVEL);
}

version_tuple getRuntimeVersion() {
#ifndef USE_STATIC_CUDNN
  int major = 0, minor = 0, patch = 0;
  cudnnGetProperty(MAJOR_VERSION, &major);
  cudnnGetProperty(MINOR_VERSION, &minor);
  cudnnGetProperty(PATCH_LEVEL, &patch);
  return version_tuple((size_t)major, (size_t)minor, (size_t)patch);
#else
  return getCompileVersion();
#endif
}

size_t getVersionInt() {
  return at::detail::getCUDAHooks().versionRuntimeCuDNN();
}
```

These are bound to Python as `torch._C._cudnn.{getRuntimeVersion, getCompileVersion, getVersionInt}`.

The Python-level compatibility checking happens in [`torch/backends/cudnn/__init__.py`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/torch/backends/cudnn/__init__.py?L36-L102), which validates that runtime and compile versions are compatible.

---

## Usage in SDPA (Scaled Dot Product Attention)

SDPA uses **runtime version checks** for feature gating. See [`aten/src/ATen/native/transformers/cuda/sdp_utils.cpp`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/aten/src/ATen/native/transformers/cuda/sdp_utils.cpp):

### Version-Based Heuristics

```cpp
bool check_cudnn_tensor_shapes(sdp_params const& params, bool debug) {
  // ... 
  long cudnn_version = at::detail::getCUDAHooks().versionRuntimeCuDNN();

  if (cudnn_version < 8903) {
    if (debug) TORCH_WARN("SDPA fprop requires cudnn 8.9.3 or higher");
    return false;
  }

  if (cudnn_version < 8906 && params.dropout != 0.0) {
    if (debug) TORCH_WARN("Dropout reference is only supported on 8.9.6 onwards.");
    return false;
  }

  auto head_dim_limit = 128;
  // Hopper: head_dim<=256 support with cuDNN >= 9.10.0
  if (cudnn_version >= 91000) {
    auto dprops = at::cuda::getCurrentDeviceProperties();
    if (dprops->major == 9 && !dprops->minor) {
      head_dim_limit = 256;
    }
  }

  // Blackwell GPUs: Special case for DeepSeek dimensions
  if (cudnn_version >= 91100) {
    auto dprops = at::cuda::getCurrentDeviceProperties();
    if (dprops->major == 10 && d_qk == 192 && d_v == 128) {
      head_dim_limit = 192;
    }
  }
  // ... more checks
}
```

**Compile-time guards** are also used ([lines 735-748](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/aten/src/ATen/native/transformers/cuda/sdp_utils.cpp?L735-L748)):

```cpp
#if defined(CUDNN_VERSION) && CUDNN_VERSION < 90000
  if (debug) {
    TORCH_WARN(CUDNN_VERSION, " cuDNN version too old to use cuDNN Attention (< v9.0.0)");
  }
  return false;
#endif

#if defined(CUDNN_VERSION)
  static auto cudnn_version = at::detail::getCUDAHooks().versionRuntimeCuDNN();
  if (params.dropout > 0.0 && cudnn_version > 91100 && cudnn_version < 91400) {
    if (debug) {
      TORCH_WARN(CUDNN_VERSION, " cuDNN version does not support dropout in SDPA (9.11 - 9.13).");
    }
    return false;
  }
#endif
```

---

## Usage in Convolution Operations

Convolutions use **both** compile-time and runtime versions for different purposes:

### 1. **Runtime Version for Feature Gating** ([`Convolution.cpp`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/aten/src/ATen/native/Convolution.cpp?L412-L419))

```cpp
bool use_cudnn(const at::Tensor& input, const at::Tensor& weight) const {
  // ...
  static long cudnn_version = detail::getCUDAHooks().versionRuntimeCuDNN();
  if (needs_64bit_indexing_no_split(input, weight)) {
    if (!(cudnn_version >= 90300 && at::native::cudnnv8_enabled_check_debug())) {
      TORCH_WARN_ONCE("cuDNN cannot be used for large non-batch-splittable convolutions"
                      " if the V8 API is not enabled or before cuDNN version 9.3+.");
      return false;
    }
  }
  // ...
}
```

### 2. **Compile-Time Version for Memory Format Selection** ([`ConvUtils.h`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/aten/src/ATen/native/ConvUtils.h?L329-L358))

```cpp
inline at::MemoryFormat cudnn_conv_suggest_memory_format(const at::Tensor& input, const at::Tensor& weight) {
  // ...
  long cudnn_version = at::detail::getCUDAHooks().versionCuDNN();  // Uses COMPILE-TIME version

  bool can_use_cudnn_channels_last_2d = (cudnn_version >= 7603) && (weight_ndim == 4) && (
    (input_memory_format  == at::MemoryFormat::ChannelsLast) ||
    (weight_memory_format == at::MemoryFormat::ChannelsLast)
  );

  bool can_use_cudnn_channels_last_3d = (cudnn_version >= 8005) && (weight_ndim == 5) && (
    (input_memory_format  == at::MemoryFormat::ChannelsLast3d) ||
    (weight_memory_format == at::MemoryFormat::ChannelsLast3d)
  );
  // ...
}
```

### 3. **Heuristic Mode Selection** ([`Conv_v8.cpp`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/aten/src/ATen/native/cudnn/Conv_v8.cpp?L858-L863))

The cuDNN V8 API uses different heuristic modes for selecting optimal algorithms:

```cpp
auto heuristic_mode = at::native::cudnnv8_use_heur_mode_b()
    ? CUDNN_HEUR_MODE_B
    : CUDNN_HEUR_MODE_INSTANT;
```

This is controlled by the `TORCH_CUDNN_USE_HEURISTIC_MODE_B` environment variable ([`ConvUtils.h`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/aten/src/ATen/native/ConvUtils.h?L74-L93)):

```cpp
bool is_cudnnv8_heuristic_mode_b() {
  static const bool is_cudnnv8_heuristic_mode_b = 
    c10::utils::check_env("TORCH_CUDNN_USE_HEURISTIC_MODE_B") == true;
  return is_cudnnv8_heuristic_mode_b;
}
```

---

## Exposing cuDNN Runtime Version in CUDA Hooks

Currently, the runtime version is **already available** through:

1. **C++ API**: `at::detail::getCUDAHooks().versionRuntimeCuDNN()`
2. **Python API**: `torch._C._cudnn.getRuntimeVersion()` (returns tuple) or `torch.backends.cudnn.version()` (returns int)

If you want to expose it more directly in the CUDA module hooks, you could add a Python binding similar to how CUDA version is exposed ([`Module.cpp`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/pytorch/pytorch/-/blob/torch/csrc/cuda/Module.cpp?L258-L264)):

```cpp
PyObject* THCPModule_getCudnnRuntimeVersion(PyObject* self, PyObject* noargs) {
#if AT_CUDNN_ENABLED()
  return THPUtils_packInt64((int64_t)at::detail::getCUDAHooks().versionRuntimeCuDNN());
#else
  Py_RETURN_NONE;
#endif
}
```

Then register it in the methods table around line 2050 and expose it via `torch.cuda` module.

### Key Takeaways

- **Compile-time version**: Used for static feature detection (e.g., memory formats)
- **Runtime version**: Used for dynamic dispatching and feature gating (e.g., SDPA dropout support, 64-bit indexing)
- **SDPA**: Uses runtime version exclusively for capability checks
- **Convolution**: Uses compile-time for memory format, runtime for 64-bit indexing and V8 API gating
- **Heuristics**: Controlled by environment variables, not version-dependent

